# Dogfood: this builder reproduces its own goal spec.
# Replay with:  goals loop build --script examples/visual-builder.loop --out .goals
# The result passes `goals loop check` clean.

objective Build a visual goal-loop builder for this repo, dogfooded with the repo's own primitives
why A visual, dogfooded builder makes goal loops easy to compose, lint, and improve across Claude and Codex
dod goals loop build, check, and improve all ship and pass tests

add Visual loop builder :: compose phases, conditions, and attached skills in a text TUI, export standalone HTML
accept A user can build a loop end to end and the written spec round-trips into goals (a test verifies it).
accept The exported HTML renders the same loop and opens standalone with no server.
terminate The builder writes a valid portable spec and the HTML export renders it.

add Loop evaluation :: lint a designed loop for issues and offer safe auto-fixes
accept Each defect class has a failing fixture the checker flags and a healthy fixture it passes clean (tests verify).
accept The --fix pass is idempotent and never edits a loop that already passes (a test verifies it).
terminate goals loop check reports a clean healthy fixture and flags every defect fixture.

add Self-improvement loop :: detect per-phase regressions with evidence and propose focused improvements
accept A simulated failed phase produces an evidence-backed memory record (a test verifies it).
accept goals loop improve turns recorded suggestions into a reviewable change set and is a no-op when nothing is approved (tests verify).
terminate Blocking vs deferred routing is verified and deferred items never auto-apply.

save
